headline.main: Annual Parade and Dinner of the Rynders Grenadiers.

docs.lead_paragraph: The independent battalion, Rynders Grenadiers, Major G. B. HALL, held their third annual parade and dinner, yesterday. The Battalion mustered nearly two hundred, all wearing the tall hear skin cap.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamer America reached Boston at 2 o'clock on Saturday afternoon. We gave a synopsis of her news in the TIMES of Friday morning, received by Telegraph from Halifax. Her mails reached this City at an early hour yesterday morning.

docs.lead_paragraph: There were buried in this City last week one hundred and thirty-three persons more than during the seven days preceding. Of these there were 31 children more under one year, 29 more between one and two years, and 41 more between two and five years than the preceding week.
